-- Kuwait Petroleum Names Farouk Al-Zanki Acting CEO, Replacing al-Shuwaib
-- B y   F i o n a   M a c D o n a l d
-- 2010-09-22T11:48:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-22/kuwait-petroleum-names-farouk-al-zanki-acting-ceo-replacing-al-shuwaib.html
Kuwait Petroleum Corp. appointed
Farouk al-Zanki as acting chief executive officer until a decree
is issued by the country’s ruler, al-Zanki said today in a phone
interview.  “I’ll be acting CEO until the issue of an emiri decree to
appoint the board of KPC,” al-Zanki said. The appointment is
effective from Sept. 26, he said.  Al-Zanki, who succeeds Saad al-Shuwaib, is the chairman and
managing director of the Kuwait National Petroleum Co., KPC’s
refining unit.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fiona MacDonald in Kuwait at 
